data.description: This is your rare opportunity to own a fully restored historic home in the Nelson/Ball Ground Area. This home was built in 1905 but professionally restored with original historical touches and high-end finishes in 2019. A ranch 3/2 home with desirable one-level living. Original wood walls throughout are painted white and accented with custom trim. Hardwood floors throughout. Custom white and gray kitchen cabinets with soft-close doors and drawers. Granite countertops, Pantry, Stainless Appliances, French Door Fridge, Gas Cooking, Built-in Microwave, Large Island Sink and Breakfast Bar, Open Dining Area.  The owner's Suite has a sliding farmhouse door connecting the En Suite Bath w large granite Double Vanity and a spacious walk-in Tile Shower ~ The Bath connects to a large Walk-in Closet, Laundry Room, with an area for an office ~ 2 Secondary Bedrooms, and Full Bath ~Level, Fenced Backyard has Gazebo and outbuilding for storage ~Excellent location just 3 minutes to I-575/515 and 5 Minutes to downtown Ball Ground, 8 minutes to downtown Jasper ~Close to Shopping, Hospital, Restaurants, wineries in Jasper or Canton, and North Georgia Mountains. Wonderful location on the Cherokee County line with Pickens County taxes. Too much character to fully describe! This is a must-see. Would be a great property for and Air Bnb. Don't miss out on this opportunity!
